  "The species that forms when a base gains an electron": "",
  "A strong base that fully dissociates in water solution": "",
  "An acid that has been diluted with a large volume of water": "",
  "A conjugate base is the species that remains after an acid has donated a proton (H+). For example, when acetic acid (CH3COOH) loses H+, it becomes acetate (CH3COO-), its conjugate base.": "",
  "What is a conjugate acid?": "",
  "A strong acid that completely dissociates in an aqueous solution": "",
